<p>Im trying to draw UIView along a circle radius and I have an issue I don't understand. the idea is to divide the circle angle by the number of UIViews I want to add and draw them along it with equal distance along the perimeter.</p>  <p>here is what I have:</p>  <pre><code>override func viewDidLoad() {         super.viewDidLoad()          // Do any additional setup after loading the view          let center_x = self.view.frame.width / 2         let center_y = self.view.frame.height / 2         let center = CGPoint(x: center_x, y: center_y)          println("Screen width center is: \(center_x) and screen height center is: \(center_y)")           var theta = 0         var r = 50          while theta &lt;= 360 {             let box = UIView()             box.backgroundColor = UIColor.blackColor()             var xpos = randomPointOnCircle(Float(theta), radius: Float(r), center: center)             println(xpos)             box.frame = CGRectMake(xpos.x - 10, xpos.y - 10, 20, 20)             box.layer.cornerRadius = 10.0             self.view.addSubview(box)             // 360 / 5 = 72             theta = theta + 72         }      }      func randomPointOnCircle(degree:Float, radius:Float, center:CGPoint) -&gt; CGPoint {         let theta = degree         // Convert polar to cartesian         let x = radius * cosf(theta)         let y = radius * sinf(theta)         return CGPointMake(CGFloat(x)+center.x,CGFloat(y)+center.y)     } </code></pre>  <p>As a result I have 6 views (instead of 5), and there are not equally spaced along the circle. </p>  <p>Do I miss something?</p>